cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper deals with predicting the type of community interested in a news article using content-based features. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the generalization of models over time, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with community-specific interest, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) or cybersecurity (cs.CY) depending on the context.
